When someone consistently follows through on their promises and shows that they are reliable, it becomes easier to trust them. On the other hand, it can be difficult to trust someone if they have betrayed your trust in the past or if their actions do not align with their words. What are your thoughts on this?
transcript_llm: Totally get where you're coming from! Consistency is key, you know. When someone walks the talk and keeps their word, it really builds that trust over time. Trust is like delicate tissue paper - easy to crumple, hard to smooth out. It's like a fragile thing, you know? Uh, have you ever had an experience where someone's consistency (or lack of it) affected your trust in them?
